# File Organization Rules

## Component Placement

- **Role-specific components** go in `src/components/{role}/` (farmer, agent, logistics, admin)
- **Cross-role shared components** go in `src/components/shared/`
- **shadcn/ui primitives** in `src/components/ui/` — NEVER edit these files
- **Feature-specific components** go in `src/components/{feature}/` (crop-diary, listings, geo)

## Page Placement

- Pages go in `src/pages/{role}/` matching the role's route prefix
- Public pages (Index, About, Contact) go in `src/pages/` root
- Auth pages go in `src/pages/Auth/`

## Hooks

- ALL hooks go in `src/hooks/` — never inside component files
- Name: `use{Feature}.tsx` (e.g., `useCropDiary.tsx`, `useTrips.tsx`)
- Every data hook uses `useQuery` / `useMutation` from TanStack Query

## Naming Conventions

- **Files**: PascalCase for components/pages, camelCase for utilities
- **One component per file**: File name = component name
- **Exports**: Named exports preferred (`export function MyComponent`)

## Route Constants

- Always use `ROUTES` from `src/lib/routes.ts` — never string literals for routes
- When adding a new page, add the route constant first

## Tailwind

- Always use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` for conditional/merged classes
- Follow spacing from `docs/ui/ui-guidelines.md`

## i18n

- ALWAYS add keys to BOTH `src/i18n/en.ts` AND `src/i18n/kn.ts` simultaneously
- Use `useLanguage()` hook and `t('key.path')` — never hardcode user-visible strings
